40|$|The {{purpose of}} the paper is to compare {{regulations}} in corporate governance codes in 27 EU countries concerning <b>remuneration</b> <b>of</b> top executives. It enables identifying two main mechanisms which are implemented in CG codes - market mechanism based on high <b>level</b> <b>of</b> <b>remuneration</b> transparency and hierarchical mechanism based on setting rules according to which corporate boards establish a formal procedure for fixing the <b>remuneration</b> packages <b>of</b> executives. The paper presents the discussion on determinants of these two mechanisms...|$|R
