40|$|The {{increasing}} role {{of healthcare}} assistants (HCAs) {{in intensive care}} in relation to patient monitoring has raised concerns among some clinical managers, particularly where such roles are not underpinned by a sound knowledge base and critical reasoning ability. This article describes a study which was undertaken {{in an attempt to}} identify how HCAs are currently utilized within the general intensive care environment. The results show a wide variation between units in relation to the activities undertaken by HCAs, their training and the <b>levels</b> <b>of</b> <b>remuneration.</b> This article seeks to open up the debate {{as to whether or not}} nurses should be challenging the nursing care that is now delivered by non-nurses and makes recommendations for the way forward in this area...|$|R
